			<description><![CDATA[<p>
	Hello!</p>
<p>
	We&rsquo;re looking for a web designer and front end developer to join a small and enthusiastic team of film-lovers who run Shooting People. We have offices based in East London and Manhattan, and are looking for someone to join us full time in our Hoxton HQ which is best described as &ldquo;hobo chic&rdquo;.</p>
<p>
	Who are we?</p>
<p>
	Shooting People is an online network that helps independent filmmakers get their films made and find the audiences they deserve through a community sharing resources, skills and experience. There are over 37,000 subscription-based members in the UK and US and 200+ films each week are cast and crewed using the services. Shooting People members can create their own profiles, upload their films, use the Independent Film Calendar, read blogs and take advantage of free filmmaking resources.</p>
<p>
	Who we work with</p>
<p>
	We&rsquo;ve worked with some top people over the last decade, including the likes of Nick Cave, Michael Winterbottom and most recently John Waters and Matt Groening. Sitting at the heart of the industry, we partner with top UK festivals (Edinburgh, Sheffield Doc/Fest, London), big venues (BFI, BAFTA) and film/arts publications (Little White Lies, The Guardian, Aesthetica).</p>
<p>
	If you have the skills, and are interested in joining our team, email us at jobs@shootingpeople.org with examples of your web design work, and a couple of paragraphs about how you&#39;ve worked on previous web projects, and what direction you&#39;d like to take the design of the Shooting People site.</p>
<p>
	We look forward to hearing from you.</p>
<p>
	Team SP</p>
<p>
	Job outline</p>
<p>
	This is a full time role, looking for an individual with both Web Design and Front End Developer skills. Salary dependant on experience.</p>
<p>
	<br />
	You will be:</p>
<p>
	initiating and implementing design strategies for the website.<br />
	developing interfaces and new site builds.<br />
	designing partnership promotions (print and web) and other branding.<br />
	updating and improving designs for existing parts of the site.</p>
<p>
	<br />
	You will need to:</p>
<p>
	know html and css.<br />
	have a strong grasp of UX design, being able to produce sensible interfaces.<br />
	ensure the layouts of each page are accessible and logical.<br />
	be excited about html5 and css3.<br />
	have an awareness of what parts of the design can be enhanced with javascript.</p>
<p>
	<br />
	The right person for us would be someone who:</p>
<p>
	enjoys working in a small and flexible team<br />
	is always keen to learn new skills<br />
	has a good portfolio of work<br />
	&nbsp;</p>
